{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 15:43:24.038195", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission successful.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- Faulty devices: host_1_1_1_1, router_dist_1_1\n- Root causes: host_missing_ip (host has no IPv4 address/DHCP lease), frr_service_down (FRR daemons on router_dist_1_1 not responding)\n\nRecommended next remediation steps (brief):\n1. On host_1_1_1_1: check DHCP client status (restart dhclient/NetworkManager), verify switch port VLAN and link, confirm other hosts in same VLAN have leases.\n2. On router_dist_1_1: check FRR service processes (zebra/ospfd), restart FRR if needed, review FRR logs, verify OSPF adjacency and that 10.1.1.0/24 is being advertised.\n3. If DHCP relay runs on router_dist_1_1, ensure it's operational so hosts can obtain leases.\n\nIf you want, I can run the follow-up diagnostics now (check FRR service status/logs on router_dist_1_1 and DHCP client status on host_1_1_1_1).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2322, "output_tokens": 245, "total_tokens": 2567, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
